To provide context, I was approached with compromising information about a company's carbon emissions. Upon investigation, I discovered that the company emits one million tonnes of CO2 more per year than what they claim. Regrettably, I succumbed to temptation and made the poor decision of accepting a bribe in exchange for not publishing this crucial information.

I want to emphasize that although my actions were reprehensible, I did not anticipate the limited duration during which the false narrative was perpetuated. Within just five weeks, another individual released the true numbers, thereby exposing the company's actual environmental impact. While this does not excuse or justify my misconduct, it does shed light on the relatively short period during which the company managed to deceive the public through their greenwashing tactics.

I approach this court today with genuine remorse for my lapse in judgment and assure you that this incident is not indicative of the person I truly am. I recognize the seriousness of my offense and the harm it has caused. I humbly request the court's leniency as I strive to make amends for my actions, learn from this experience, and work towards becoming a better individual.

Respectfully,

Jack Palmer
